    <text id="B1077T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell forwards a list of Bureau employees in his district to Brown in
                    Richmond.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District
                    Department of the Potomac
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt. Brig.
                        Gen.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst.
                        Comr.</abbr><lb/>Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-09-11"><abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 11th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>In compliance with Circular Letter from your HeadQuarters dated Septr 3rd 1867: I
                    have the honor to transmit a List of Employees in this District, showing their
                    duties, names, place where employed, born, and places whence appointed, with
                    annual compensation of each.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obet</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Captain &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
